<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-04T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-04T13:00:00-05:00" n="823" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d823">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.51/1284a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-04T13:00:00-05:00">December 4, 1940—1
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>216. With Reference to press reports that the Chilean Government has
                            officially suspended amortization of the foreign debt to divert funds to
                            the Exchange Control Commission, please expedite full report.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>